## 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Rapid Revision Checklist — Must Memorize for KTU Lab Exam**

- **Queue** = **FIFO** discipline; insertions at `rear`, deletions at `front`.
- **Linear queue** uses simple `rear = rear + 1` — suffers from **false overflow**.
- **Circular queue** uses **`(rear + 1) % MAX`** — reuses freed slots.
- **Empty circular queue** → `front == -1`.
- **Full circular queue** → `(rear + 1) % MAX == front` (one slot is always sacrificed).
- **Empty linear queue** → `front == -1` or `front > rear` (after reset).
- **Full linear queue** → `rear == MAX - 1`.
- **Time complexity** of both enqueue and dequeue is **O(1)**.
- **Space complexity** is **O(N)** where `N = MAX`.
- Always handle the **first-element insertion special case** (`front == -1` → set `front = 0`).
- Always **reset `front = rear = -1`** after deleting the last element to avoid incorrect state.
- **Use `(front + 1) % MAX` and `(rear + 1) % MAX`** — never use `front++` or `rear++` in circular queue increment.
- The **display function** must traverse only valid elements using the count formula `(MAX - front + rear) % MAX` for circular queues.
- **Real-world**: CPU scheduling, print spooling, network buffering, OS kernel ring buffers.

