**Q.A (b) [7 Marks]** Write a C function to **search** for a given key `k` in a doubly linked list and return the position of the **first occurrence**. If the key is not found, return `-1`. Analyze its time complexity.

**Model Solution:**

```c
int search(int key) {
    struct Node* temp = head;
    int position = 1;       /* 1-indexed position (KTU standard) */
    while (temp != NULL) {
        if (temp->data == key) {
            return position;  /* Found */
        }
        temp = temp->next;
        position++;
    }
    return -1;  /* Not found */
}
```

**Time Complexity Analysis:**

$$
\begin{aligned}
T(n) &= \text{Number of comparisons in worst case} \\
&= n \quad (\text{key at last position or not present}) \\
\therefore \quad T(n) &= O(n)
\end{aligned}
$$

**Space Complexity:** $O(1)$ (only a single temporary pointer is used).

**Mark Distribution (7 marks):**
- Function signature & initialization (1 mark)
- Traversal loop (2 marks)
- Comparison & return logic (2 marks)
- Time complexity analysis (2 marks)

