**(b) C Function for Polynomial Evaluation (7 marks)**:

The mathematical formula for evaluation is:

$$P(x_0) = \sum_{i=0}^{k-1} a_i \cdot (x_0)^{e_i}$$

The C implementation:

```c
int evaluate(struct Node *head, int x0) {
    int result = 0;
    struct Node *temp = head;
    while (temp != NULL) {
        /* Compute (x0)^expo using a fast helper loop */
        int power = 1, j;
        for (j = 0; j < temp->expo; j++) power *= x0;
        result += temp->coeff * power;          // (1 mark for the term contribution)
        temp = temp->next;                      // (1 mark for traversal)
    }
    return result;                              // (1 mark for correct return)
}
```

**Mark distribution**: (1) Correct function signature and return type — **1 mark**. (2) Loop traversal over all nodes — **1 mark**. (3) Power calculation $x_0^{e_i}$ — **2 marks**. (4) Coefficient multiplication and accumulation — **1 mark**. (5) Return statement and edge case handling (empty list returns 0) — **1 mark**. (6) Code quality, indentation, and comments — **1 mark**.

