> **Rapid Revision Checklist — Must Memorize for KTU 2024**

- **Node structure**: `coeff` (int) + `expo` (int) + `next` (pointer). Total **3 fields**.
- **Storage order**: Always **descending exponents** (highest degree first) for $O(n+m)$ merge addition.
- **Three merge rules**: Equal exponent → **add coefficients**; P₁ higher → **copy P₁**; P₂ higher → **copy P₂**.
- **Zero-sum suppression**: If `coeff1 + coeff2 == 0` after merging equal exponents, **skip the node creation**.
- **Time complexity of addition**: $O(n + m)$, **single linear pass**, no nested loops.
- **Space complexity**: $O(n + m)$ for the resultant list, $O(k)$ for sparse storage.
- **Memory hygiene**: Always call `freeList()` on every dynamically created list to avoid **memory leaks** (a 2-mark deduction in ESE).
- **Edge cases to test**: (1) Empty polynomial, (2) polynomials of unequal lengths, (3) all exponents cancel out (result is the zero polynomial), (4) negative coefficients, (5) constant-term-only polynomial.
- **Display formatting**: Use `abs()` for coefficient magnitude and **print signs explicitly** (`+` or `-`) when traversing non-head nodes.
- **Why not array?** Array wastes $O(n)$ space for sparse polynomials; linked list uses only $O(k)$.
- **Sorting invariant**: If user input is not sorted, call an `insertSorted()` helper to maintain descending exponent order **before** addition — a common viva question.

