## 3. Step-by-Step Derivations & Analytical Matrix

### 3.1 Exhaustive Worked Example — Build a BST

**Insertion sequence:** `50, 30, 70, 20, 40, 60, 80`

**Step-by-step derivation:**

$$\text{Step 1: Insert 50} \implies \text{root} = 50$$

$$\text{Step 2: Insert 30} \implies 30 < 50 \implies \text{go left of 50, empty spot} \implies 50\text{.left} = 30$$

$$\text{Step 3: Insert 70} \implies 70 > 50 \implies \text{go right of 50, empty spot} \implies 50\text{.right} = 70$$

$$\text{Step 4: Insert 20} \implies 20 < 50 \to \text{left} \implies 20 < 30 \to \text{left} \implies 30\text{.left} = 20$$

$$\text{Step 5: Insert 40} \implies 40 < 50 \to \text{left} \implies 40 > 30 \to \text{right} \implies 30\text{.right} = 40$$

$$\text{Step 6: Insert 60} \implies 60 > 50 \to \text{right} \implies 60 < 70 \to \text{left} \implies 70\text{.left} = 60$$

$$\text{Step 7: Insert 80} \implies 80 > 50 \to \text{right} \implies 80 > 70 \to \text{right} \implies 70\text{.right} = 80$$

**Final BST Structure:**

```
            50
           /  \
         30    70
        /  \   / \
      20   40 60  80
```

**Verification via In-order Traversal (Left → Root → Right):**
$$20 \to 30 \to 40 \to 50 \to 60 \to 70 \to 80 \quad \text{(Strictly sorted ✓)}$$

### 3.2 Exhaustive Deletion Walkthrough

**Delete operations on the above BST in order: Delete 20, Delete 30, Delete 50**

#### 3.2.1 Delete 20 (Case 0: Leaf Node)

$$\text{Node 20 has no children} \implies \text{Set parent } (30)\text{.left} = \text{NULL}$$

After: `20 is removed; 30 now has no left child.`

#### 3.2.2 Delete 30 (Case 1: One Child — only right child `40`)

$$\text{Node 30 has only right child } 40 \implies \text{Replace 30 with 40}$$

After:

```
            50
           /  \
         40    70
              / \
             60  80
```

#### 3.2.3 Delete 50 (Case 2: Two Children) — The Critical Case

**Step A:** Identify the node to delete = `50` (root, has two children).
**Step B:** Find **in-order successor** = *smallest value in the right subtree*.

$$\text{Right subtree root} = 70 \implies \text{Go left: } 70\text{.left} = 60 \implies 60\text{.left} = \text{NULL} \implies \text{Successor} = 60$$

**Step C:** Copy `60` into the root node: `50 → 60`.
**Step D:** Recursively delete the original `60` from the right subtree — `60` is a **leaf** → **Case 0 deletion**.

After:

```
            60
           /  \
         40    70
                \
                 80
```

### 3.3 Complete Reference C Implementation

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

/* ---------- Node Definition ---------- */
struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node *left;
    struct Node *right;
};

/* ---------- Create New Node ---------- */
struct Node* createNode(int value) {
    struct Node *newNode = (struct Node *)malloc(sizeof(struct Node));
    newNode->data  = value;
    newNode->left  = NULL;
    newNode->right = NULL;
    return newNode;
}

/* ---------- Insertion (Recursive) ---------- */
struct Node* insert(struct Node *root, int value) {
    if (root == NULL)
        return createNode(value);

    if (value < root->data)
        root->left  = insert(root->left,  value);
    else if (value > root->data)
        root->right = insert(root->right, value);
    /* duplicates are ignored */
    return root;
}

/* ---------- Search (Recursive) ---------- */
struct Node* search(struct Node *root, int key) {
    if (root == NULL || root->data == key)
        return root;
    if (key < root->data)
        return search(root->left, key);
    return search(root->right, key);
}

/* ---------- Find Minimum (used in deletion) ---------- */
struct Node* findMin(struct Node *node) {
    while (node->left != NULL)
        node = node->left;
    return node;
}

/* ---------- Deletion (Recursive - 3 cases) ---------- */
struct Node* deleteNode(struct Node *root, int key) {
    if (root == NULL) return root;

    if (key < root->data)
        root->left  = deleteNode(root->left,  key);
    else if (key > root->data)
        root->right = deleteNode(root->right, key);
    else {
        /* Case 0 & Case 1: No child or one child */
        if (root->left == NULL) {
            struct Node *temp = root->right;
            free(root);
            return temp;
        } else if (root->right == NULL) {
            struct Node *temp = root->left;
            free(root);
            return temp;
        }
        /* Case 2: Two children */
        struct Node *temp = findMin(root->right);          // in-order successor
        root->data = temp->data;
        root->right = deleteNode(root->right, temp->data); // delete successor
    }
    return root;
}

/* ---------- Traversals ---------- */
void inorder(struct Node *root) {
    if (root != NULL) {
        inorder(root->left);
        printf("%d ", root->data);
        inorder(root->right);
    }
}
void preorder(struct Node *root) {
    if (root != NULL) {
        printf("%d ", root->data);
        preorder(root->left);
        preorder(root->right);
    }
}
void postorder(struct Node *root) {
    if (root != NULL) {
        postorder(root->left);
        postorder(root->right);
        printf("%d ", root->data);
    }
}

/* ---------- Driver / Tester ---------- */
int main(void) {
    struct Node *root = NULL;
    int values[] = {50, 30, 70, 20, 40, 60, 80};
    int n = sizeof(values) / sizeof(values[0]);

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        root = insert(root, values[i]);

    printf("Inorder  : "); inorder(root);  printf("\n");
    printf("Preorder : "); preorder(root); printf("\n");
    printf("Postorder: "); postorder(root);printf("\n");

    int key = 40;
    printf("Search %d : %s\n", key,
           search(root, key) ? "FOUND" : "NOT FOUND");

    root = deleteNode(root, 20);
    root = deleteNode(root, 30);
    root = deleteNode(root, 50);
    printf("After deletions, Inorder: ");
    inorder(root);
    printf("\n");

    return 0;
}
```

### 3.4 Output Trace for the Driver

```
Inorder  : 20 30 40 50 60 70 80 
Preorder : 50 30 20 40 70 60 80 
Postorder: 20 40 30 60 80 70 50 
Search 40 : FOUND
After deletions, Inorder: 40 60 70 80 
```

### 3.5 Analytical Matrix — Operation Behaviour

| Operation | Pre-Condition | Invariant Maintained? | Return Value | Stack Depth (Recursive) |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `createNode` | Valid `malloc` | N/A (new node isolated) | Pointer to new node | $O(1)$ |
| `insert` | Non-duplicate key | Yes (BST property) | Updated root | $O(h)$ |
| `search` | None | Yes (read-only) | Node pointer or `NULL` | $O(h)$ |
| `deleteNode` | Key exists or not | Yes (BST property) | Updated root | $O(h)$ |
| Traversals | None | Yes (read-only) | `void` | $O(n)$ |

