> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Pitfalls — Where Students Lose Marks:**
> 1. **Confusing successor vs predecessor:** Some students use the *parent* or *largest in left subtree* incorrectly. Memorise: successor = `findMin(root->right)`; predecessor = `findMax(root->left)`.
> 2. **Forgetting to free memory:** In C programs, examiners deduct marks if `free(node)` is missing — memory leak in lab viva.
> 3. **Not showing the tree diagram after EACH deletion:** KTU award full marks only when **intermediate states** are clearly drawn.
> 4. **Mixing up the three traversals:** Pre-order = NLR, In-order = LNR, Post-order = LRN. A common error is writing in-order sequence as the tree itself.
> 5. **Forgetting to handle the empty tree case** (`root == NULL`) in insert/search/delete functions — instant 1–2 mark deduction.
> 6. **Writing iterative search incorrectly:** Two pointers (`current` and `parent`) are required if you also need to delete the searched node later.

