# 🔬 SECTION 3: Step-by-Step Algorithm, Derivation & Complete KTU Lab Programs

## 3.1 PROGRAM 1 — Expression Tree (Complete KTU Model Program)

### 3.1.1 Step-by-Step Algorithm

**Phase 1: Infix → Postfix (Shunting-Yard using stack of chars)**

| Input Token | Stack (top→bottom) | Action |
|---|---|---|
| Operand | unchanged | Output directly |
| `(` | push `(` | Push |
| `)` | pop till `(` | Pop all until `(`, discard `(` |
| Operator | pop higher-or-equal precedence, then push | Compare with stack top |

**Precedence table (KTU standard):**

| Operator | Precedence | Associativity |
|---|---|---|
| `^` | 3 (highest) | Right |
| `*`, `/`, `%` | 2 | Left |
| `+`, `-` | 1 (lowest) | Left |

**Phase 2: Build Expression Tree from Postfix**

```
Initialize empty stack of node pointers
For each token t in postfix expression:
    If t is operand:
        Create new node with value t
        Push node onto stack
    Else (t is operator):
        right = pop()
        left = pop()
        Create new node with value t
        Set node->left = left, node->right = right
        Push new node onto stack
At end, stack top is the ROOT of the expression tree
```

**Phase 3: Evaluate Expression Tree (Post-order recursion)**

$$\text{eval}(\text{node}) = \begin{cases} \text{node.value} & \text{if leaf (operand)} \\ \text{eval(left)} \odot \text{eval(right)} & \text{if internal (operator)} \end{cases}$$

### 3.1.2 Complete Working C Program (KTU Lab Standard)

```c
/* ======================================================
   KTU PCITL308 - Module Experiment 2
   Application: Expression Tree (Infix Expression Evaluator)
   Algorithm : Infix -> Postfix -> Expression Tree -> Evaluate
   ====================================================== */
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <ctype.h>
#include <math.h>

#define MAX 100

/* ---------- Global stacks ---------- */
char  postfix[MAX];
int   topPost = -1;
char  opStack[MAX];
int   topOp   = -1;

/* ---------- Expression Tree Node ---------- */
struct Node {
    char  data;             /* operator or digit character */
    struct Node *left;
    struct Node *right;
};

/* ---------- Postfix stack helpers ---------- */
void pushPost(char c) { postfix[++topPost] = c; }
char popPost(void)    { return postfix[topPost--]; }

/* ---------- Operator stack helpers ---------- */
void pushOp(char c)   { opStack[++topOp] = c; }
char popOp(void)      { return opStack[topOp--]; }
char peekOp(void)     { return opStack[topOp]; }

/* ---------- Precedence & associativity ---------- */
int precedence(char op) {
    if (op == '^') return 3;
    if (op == '*' || op == '/' || op == '%') return 2;
    if (op == '+' || op == '-') return 1;
    return 0;
}
int isRightAssociative(char op) { return (op == '^'); }

/* ---------- Step 1: Infix -> Postfix ---------- */
void infixToPostfix(char infix[]) {
    int i;
    char c, top;
    topPost = -1;  topOp = -1;

    for (i = 0; infix[i] != '\0'; i++) {
        c = infix[i];

        if (isdigit(c) || isalpha(c)) {
            pushPost(c);
        }
        else if (c == '(') {
            pushOp(c);
        }
        else if (c == ')') {
            while (topOp != -1 && peekOp() != '(')
                pushPost(popOp());
            popOp();   /* discard '(' */
        }
        else { /* operator */
            while (topOp != -1 && peekOp() != '(' &&
                  (precedence(peekOp()) > precedence(c) ||
                  (precedence(peekOp()) == precedence(c) && !isRightAssociative(c))))
                pushPost(popOp());
            pushOp(c);
        }
    }
    while (topOp != -1) pushPost(popOp());
    postfix[topPost + 1] = '\0';
}

/* ---------- Step 2: Build expression tree from postfix ---------- */
struct Node* buildTree(char post[]) {
    struct Node *stack[MAX];
    int top = -1;
    struct Node *node, *left, *right;
    int i;

    for (i = 0; post[i] != '\0'; i++) {
        char c = post[i];
        node = (struct Node*)malloc(sizeof(struct Node));
        node->data = c;
        node->left = node->right = NULL;

        if (isdigit(c) || isalpha(c)) {
            stack[++top] = node;                 /* leaf */
        } else {
            right = stack[top--];                 /* IMPORTANT: right first */
            left  = stack[top--];
            node->right = right;
            node->left  = left;
            stack[++top] = node;
        }
    }
    return stack[top];
}

/* ---------- Step 3: Recursive traversals ---------- */
void inorder(struct Node* r) {
    if (r == NULL) return;
    if (!isdigit(r->data) && !isalpha(r->data)) printf("(");
    inorder(r->left);
    printf("%c", r->data);
    inorder(r->right);
    if (!isdigit(r->data) && !isalpha(r->data)) printf(")");
}
void preorder(struct Node* r) {
    if (r == NULL) return;
    printf("%c", r->data);
    preorder(r->left);
    preorder(r->right);
}
void postorder(struct Node* r) {
    if (r == NULL) return;
    postorder(r->left);
    postorder(r->right);
    printf("%c", r->data);
}

/* ---------- Step 4: Evaluate expression tree ---------- */
int evaluate(struct Node* r) {
    if (r == NULL) return 0;
    if (isdigit(r->data)) return r->data - '0';

    int leftVal  = evaluate(r->left);
    int rightVal = evaluate(r->right);

    switch (r->data) {
        case '+': return leftVal + rightVal;
        case '-': return leftVal - rightVal;
        case '*': return leftVal * rightVal;
        case '/': return (rightVal != 0) ? leftVal / rightVal : 0;
        case '^': return (int)pow((double)leftVal, (double)rightVal);
    }
    return 0;
}

/* ---------- Free tree ---------- */
void freeTree(struct Node* r) {
    if (r == NULL) return;
    freeTree(r->left);
    freeTree(r->right);
    free(r);
}

/* ---------- Main driver ---------- */
int main(void) {
    char infix[MAX];
    struct Node *root = NULL;

    printf("Enter infix expression (single digit operands, no spaces): ");
    scanf("%s", infix);

    infixToPostfix(infix);
    printf("Postfix  : %s\n", postfix);

    root = buildTree(postfix);

    printf("Inorder  : "); inorder(root);   printf("\n");
    printf("Preorder : "); preorder(root);  printf("\n");
    printf("Postorder: "); postorder(root); printf("\n");

    printf("Evaluated Result = %d\n", evaluate(root));

    freeTree(root);
    return 0;
}
```

### 3.1.3 Sample Dry Run

**Input:** `5+(3*2)-4^2`

**Phase 1 → Postfix Conversion:**

| Token | Action | Postfix output | Op stack |
|---|---|---|---|
| `5` | Operand → output | `5` | empty |
| `+` | Push | `5` | `+` |
| `(` | Push | `5` | `+  (` |
| `3` | Operand | `5 3` | `+  (` |
| `*` | Push | `5 3` | `+  (  *` |
| `2` | Operand | `5 3 2` | `+  (  *` |
| `)` | Pop till `(` | `5 3 2 *` | `+` |
| `-` | `+` popped (≥ prec) | `5 3 2 * +` | `-` |
| `4` | Operand | `5 3 2 * + 4` | `-` |
| `^` | Push | `5 3 2 * + 4` | `-  ^` |
| `2` | Operand | `5 3 2 * + 4 2` | `-  ^` |
| end | Pop all | `5 3 2 * + 4 2 ^ -` | empty |

**Resulting postfix:** `532*+42^-`

**Expected output of program:**

```
Postfix  : 532*+42^-
Inorder  : 5+3*2-4^2
Preorder : -+5*32^42
Postorder: 532*+42^-
Evaluated Result = 5
```

$$\text{Evaluation: } 5 + (3 \times 2) - (4^2) = 5 + 6 - 16 = -5$$

