## 🔹 Part B — Long Answer Questions (14 Marks Each) — Internal Choice

### **Question A (14 Marks) `[KTU University Exam – May 2024]`**

**(a)** Explain the algorithm to convert an infix expression to a postfix expression using a stack. Trace the algorithm for the infix expression: `A + B * C - D / E`. **(7 marks)**

**(b)** Using the postfix expression obtained, construct the expression tree. List all three depth-first traversals and verify that the in-order traversal reproduces the original infix expression. **(7 marks)**

**Model Solution:**

**(a) Algorithm (7 marks):**

**Algorithm: Infix to Postfix Conversion**

1. Initialize two empty stacks — one for operators (`opStack`), one for output (`postfix`).
2. Scan the infix string left to right.
3. **If token is operand** → append to `postfix`.
4. **If token is `(`** → push to `opStack`.
5. **If token is `)`** → pop and append operators to `postfix` until `(` is found. Discard the `(`.
6. **If token is operator `op`**:
   - While `opStack` is not empty AND top of `opStack` has precedence ≥ `op` (and same precedence with left associativity) → pop top and append to `postfix`.
   - Push `op` onto `opStack`.
7. After scanning, pop all remaining operators from `opStack` to `postfix`.

**Trace for `A + B * C - D / E`:**

| Token | Action | Postfix output | opStack (top→bottom) |
|---|---|---|---|
| A | Operand | A | — |
| + | Push | A | + |
| B | Operand | AB | + |
| * | Push | AB | + * |
| C | Operand | ABC | + * |
| - | Pop `*` (prec 2 ≥ 1) → push `-` | ABC* | + - |
| D | Operand | ABC*D | + - |
| / | Push | ABC*D | + - / |
| E | Operand | ABC*DE | + - / |
| end | Pop `/`, pop `-` | ABC*DE/-+ | — |

**Final Postfix:** `ABC*DE/+-` ✅

**(b) Tree Construction & Traversals (7 marks):**

**Step-by-step tree building from `ABC*DE/+-`:**

```mermaid
graph TD
    T1[minus] --> T2[plus]
    T1 --> T3[slash]
    T2 --> T4[A]
    T2 --> T5[star]
    T3 --> T6[D]
    T3 --> T7[E]
    T5 --> T8[B]
    T5 --> T9[C]
```

**Traversals:**

| Traversal | Result | Marks |
|---|---|---|
| Inorder (with parentheses) | `A + B * C - D / E` | 2 |
| Preorder | `- + A * B C / D E` | 2 |
| Postorder | `A B C * + D E / -` (matches `ABC*DE/+-`) | 2 |
| Verification note | In-order == original infix | 1 |

