- [x] **In-order traversal of Expression Tree = original infix expression** (with parentheses).
- [x] **Pre-order traversal** is used to **copy/serialize** a tree; **Post-order** is used to **delete/free** a tree.
- [x] **Three delete cases** in BST: (1) leaf, (2) one child → bypass, (3) two children → replace with inorder successor.
- [x] **Search/Insert/Delete** in BST: $O(\log n)$ average, $O(n)$ worst-case (skewed tree).
- [x] **Build expression tree from postfix:** operand → push; operator → pop right, pop left, make them children, push.
- [x] **Right child must be popped BEFORE left child** during tree construction (stack order).
- [x] **Operator precedence** in KTU labs: `^` (3) > `*, /, %` (2) > `+, -` (1); `^` is right-associative.
- [x] **Always `free()` deleted nodes** and assign parent pointer properly to avoid dangling pointers.
- [x] **Use `malloc(sizeof(struct Node))` inside helper functions** to keep `main()` clean.
- [x] **Recursion depth** = tree height; for very deep (skewed) trees, iterative versions are preferred in production.
- [x] **Time complexity for full traversal** of $n$ nodes = $O(n)$ for any binary tree.

